    <div class="tip-block">
      <div class="tip-lbl">⚠️ Commercial oven igniter failure — common misdiagnosis</div>
      <p>A commercial gas oven that won't light or lights then goes out is most commonly an igniter failure — not a gas valve failure. Commercial igniters are high-current devices that weaken over time. We test igniter amperage draw before recommending a gas valve replacement. A failed igniter costs $80–$200 in parts; a gas valve costs $200–$600. Getting the diagnosis right matters.</p>
